(40, 0, '1', 'EG0025542 Eco Impression', 'Need to update email to: eaccustomercreations@gmail.com\n\nSpoke with Deepika about this issue:\nWe can''t save the customer prints as the system is throwing an error "can''t save because email is not valid"\nPlease update system to accept all email accounts.\n\nThanks\n\nMichael', 3, 2, '1442340738', '', '2015-09-15 12:42:18'),
(41, 0, '1', 'EG0025542 Ed Caro', 'his email address was updated fine. problem is, his picture and prints I had taken were deleted, and I can''t take a new picture, therefore I am unable to register new prints', 6, 8, '1442346552', '', '2015-09-15 14:19:12'),
(42, 1, '1', 'early termination fees', 'When a member needs to cancel within their term, and a $200 fee applies, does that charge come the day of cancelation? or does it come in 30 days?', 2, 8, '1442350580', '', '2015-09-15 15:26:20'),
(43, 0, '3', 'camera', 'I cannot register any new prints for members due to the inability to capture an image.', 3, 8, '1442358799', '', '2015-09-15 17:43:19'),
(44, 0, '1', 'Members having difficulty logging into their accounts (Eric Kozlowski EG0013728)', 'Eric Kozlowski , EG0013728, could not log into his account. I have also had other members complain.\n\nPlease attempt his login credentials:\n\nUsername: koz.eric, perhaps (Koz.eric)\nPassword: Boceans35\n\n-Chris', 3, 10, '1442419175', '', '2015-09-16 10:29:35'),
(45, 0, '1', 'Steve Janus EG0010068', 'Please delete duplicate member Steve Janus EG0010068 in Naperville and refund $38.97 to the card ending in 7117.\n\n-Chris', 3, 10, '1442419247', '', '2015-09-16 10:30:47'),
(46, 1, '1', 'member online access', 'a few members have brought to my attention that when they log onto eco gym to check their workouts, they are just getting error messages. Is there anything I can tell them in terms of a timeline of when the site will be back up and running?', 1, 8, '1442424141', '', '2015-09-16 11:52:21'),
(47, 1, '3', 'cannot take picture', 'I am unable to take a members picture and save their fingerprints. Is there anything to do on my end?', 1, 8, '1442428108', '', '2015-09-16 12:58:28'),
(48, 0, '1', 'EG0023986 Manal Mirza', 'Please issue a refund to the above account of $120 (4 months of $30 each). She should have been canceled in late April because she moved back downtown for school. It is understood that her May payment should stand. June, July, August, and September need to be refunded', 3, 8, '1442429286', '', '2015-09-16 13:18:06'),
(49, 0, '1', 'Connor Marchetti EG0035225 and Samantha Marchetti EG0035231', 'Members are currently enrolled at Plainfield, but only use Naperville.  Please transfer both memberships to Naperville.', 3, 7, '1442430785', '', '2015-09-16 13:43:05'),
(50, 0, '1', 'Membership Cancellation for School In Chicago: EG0034949 Kiran Shaikh', 'Member was enrolled with GTC up front to waive $79. She gave Marie 30 days notice to cancel that reoccurring service and was billed once extra month of $30. She has a decline transaction of $59 and has relocated to the city for school. Cancel Request has been approved. I have worked with member to charge difference of $59 and $30=$29 for last month''s dues to suffice the cancellation. Please process $29 for last month''s dues and proceed with planned cancellation of membership to due relocation for school. Thank you.', 3, 9, '1442433446', '', '2015-09-16 14:27:26'),
(51, 0, '1', 'EG0035038-Anjilita Lopez', 'Member ID # EG0035038 never activated successfully. She will not be joining at this time. Please cancel member with no additional charges. Thank you', 3, 9, '1442442118', '', '2015-09-16 16:51:58'),
(52, 0, '1', 'Bhavin Patel EG0013695', 'Member was charged $19 when he worked out over 26 times, but the scanner system was not working for the last week and never recorded workouts.  Please refund.', 3, 7, '1442442623', '', '2015-09-16 17:00:23'),
(53, 0, '1', 'EG0035304', 'Member ID EG0035304. Please make sure member expires on scheduled 9/29/15 and is not billed further on 9/29/15. Thank you.', 3, 9, '1442443580', '', '2015-09-16 17:16:20'),
(54, 1, '1', 'report analytics', 'When click the button to export to exel, nothing is happening. Am I doing something wrong?', 1, 8, '1442511675', '', '2015-09-17 12:11:15'),
(55, 0, '1', 'Joe Jablonski EG0025078', 'Joe was on a summer college membership. He paid in full $200 in May. He was then charged another $200 in september. please reverse the september $200. thank you', 3, 8, '1442520567', '', '2015-09-17 14:39:27'),
(56, 0, '1', 'J Emery EG0025533', 'J came in and had do take advantage of our 14 day money back service guarantee. When I tried to process the request, I got the following message at the top of the screen, "Error occured while processing the Refund. Error is:Transaction ID is invalid.". Please make sure cancelation was processed successfully and his refund was issued', 3, 8, '1442521410', '', '2015-09-17 14:53:30'),
(57, 0, '1', 'Carly Quick EG0013409', 'Please refund last 2 payments and cancel out immediately.  Member went to college and was supposed to be canceled.', 3, 7, '1442521537', '', '2015-09-17 14:55:37'),
(58, 0, '1', 'Joe Jablonski EG0023547', 'This is a duplicate account for a member who should be cancelled. Please delete', 3, 8, '1442521582', '', '2015-09-17 14:56:22'),
(59, 0, '1', 'Marcelina Moczybroda EG0023799', 'Marcelina had cancelled with former staff in May but continued to get billed. She understands that Junes payment should still be there, but we need to refund her July, August, and September.', 3, 8, '1442533294', '', '2015-09-17 18:11:34'),
(60, 0, '1', 'John Clark: EG0035575', '1) Member EG0035575 signed up for a Flex with Marie Tilton on 9/17/15. Called back immediately on 9/17/15 to switch to $39 fixed rate for 18 months. Was charged $118.03 instead of $119. Please look into this for future Flex with GTC payments being processed as I do not know if there is an issue or not on this or not. \n\n2) Please switch member to fixed $39 with GTC and bill remaining $19.97 ($138-$118.03) Thank you. \n\nFYI: I have already removed GTC reoccurring myself as member only wanted first two months and no reoccurring due to his work schedule not lining up with any classes. Thank you', 3, 9, '1442594959', '', '2015-09-18 11:19:19'),
(61, 0, '1', 'EG0034342: Two Child Add On''s', 'Member Maureen Gansz EG0034342 enrolled in January as a fixed $19 with three child add on''s on her account. At the time, member was not comfortable with having an EFT and would come into the club to pay all $76 in person each month on her scheduled bill date with her Credit Card. She dropped one child add on and wanted to keep the other two on. I informed member we will need an EFT moving forward with the new software and she was ok with that. \n\n She is responsible for all three monthly payments totaling $59.91 currently. Her two add ons were not being billed as join actives and they are currently in no join status. I would like to process each no join on 9/25/15, which is her reoccurring bill date for $19.97 per member only. System will automatically bill first and last month''s up front $39.94 and I do not want to over charge her as she paid first and last month for each member when she joined ($342). \n\nMember Names and ID''s\n\nEdgar Gansz EG0034344: $19.97\nJacob Gansz EG0034345: $19.97\n\nCharge card ending 9532 exp. 12/17\n\nThank you', 3, 9, '1442595708', '', '2015-09-18 11:31:48'),
(62, 0, '1', 'Nida Shaikh EG0034948', 'Please remove decline $14.99 (pro-rated GTC charge). Member gave me 30 days notice and I did not process in time. Member does not owe $14.99 due to operational error on my end. Please make sure she is returned to Join Active Status. Thank you.', 3, 9, '1442596057', '', '2015-09-18 11:37:37'),
(63, 0, '1', 'EG0034897 Camille Alvino', 'Member is canceling from Plainfield and transferring to Naperville', 5, 7, '1442596801', '', '2015-09-18 11:50:01'),
(64, 0, '1', 'UI Guest Pages Valentine''s, February 2015 Offer', 'Please remove. It has been posted since February 2015.\n\nThanks\n\nMichael', 3, 2, '1442606488', '', '2015-09-18 14:31:28'),
(65, 0, '1', 'UI Guest Screens - 7 Day Pass', 'After a customer enrolls for a 7 day pass, they have to sign a waiver of liability. Once they sign the waiver, they have access to the entire 1-2 page legal agreement of our membership. They should not have the ability to view this. Please remove this portion of visibility to all customers.\n\nThanks\n\nMichael', 3, 2, '1442606585', '', '2015-09-18 14:33:05'),
(66, 1, '3', 'deactivation', 'we have several members who have had their fingerprints deactivated even though they are active, paying members. I have gone ahead and reactivated their prints, but the next day they were deactivated again. Please stop deactivating people who i have reactivated. \n\nside note, my prints were also deactivated again this morning.', 1, 8, '1442610226', '', '2015-09-18 15:33:46'),
(67, 0, '1', 'Neil Uhler EG0022128', 'member is in cancelled status. Should not be. please reactivate membership and continue billing as usual', 3, 8, '1442610306', '', '2015-09-18 15:35:06'),
(68, 0, '1', 'Stephanie Uhler EG0023447', 'member is in cancelled status but should not be. please reactivate member and continue billing as usual', 3, 8, '1442610359', '', '2015-09-18 15:35:59'),
(69, 0, '3', 'Deactivating Staff and Customers with no reason', 'Dylan Brown prints were deactivated 9/16 and 9/18\n - on 9/18 prints were showing as deactivated but the pin code worked\n\nCustomers deactivated over the past few days and have no issues in Eco Gym Member database - more may exist:\nEG0023874\nEG0024912', 3, 2, '1442612688', '', '2015-09-18 16:14:48'),
(70, 0, '1', 'Personal Training Client with Free Membership', 'EG0021866\n\nThis customer has had a free membership since joined because she has purchased near $20K in personal training.\n\nPlease remove inactive status and all failed payments. Please reactivate membership billing starting January 21st, 2016.\n\nThanks\n\nMichael', 3, 2, '1442612791', '', '2015-09-18 16:16:31'),
(71, 0, '3', 'Prints Deactivated', 'EG0024232\n\nCustomers is active in Eco Gym and account was deactivated in EI\n\nPlease resolve this and find the root cause to fix all other issues\n\nThanks\n\nMichael', 3, 2, '1442613023', '', '2015-09-18 16:20:23'),
(72, 1, '1', 'the Uhlers', 'Who cancelled stephanie and neil uhler''s membership accounts? is there any reason for this happening?', 1, 8, '1442613295', '', '2015-09-18 16:24:55'),
(73, 0, '1', 'EG0035130', 'Taylor Zvokel EG0035130 joined as a college three month membership and paid $39.94 on 5/21/15 and $19.97 on 6/19. On 7/19, she shows a 0 transaction, but was still billed for reoccurring when she was not supposed to be. We were not offering a three month seasonal $200 at this time. \n\nShe is an add on under primary members Tracey LaFaire (EG0033998) and Robert Lafaire (EG0033999) for $19.97. Her brother Jake Novacek EG0035131 shows expired in system and paid $39.94 on 5/21 and $19.97 on 6/19. It then shows a 0 transaction for him on 7/19/15, but I do not see a cancel request that was put in from my end. I am assuming the 0 transaction means, they both should have expired on 7/19/15 with no further billing? Please advise. \n\nPlease refund last two months of $19.97=$39.94 for member ID EG0035130 as she has gone to college in August and should have expired like member ID EG0035131. Thank you.', 3, 9, '1442858285', '', '2015-09-21 12:28:05'),
